#Text=US astronomers announce discovering ten tiny Jovian satellites
#Text=Thursday , July 19 , 2018
#Text=On Tuesday , astronomers of the Carnegie Institution for Science in Washington , DC , United States , announced the discovery of ten small satellites orbiting Jupiter .
#Text=With this discovery , Jupiter now has 79 known satellites .

#Text=The team led by Scott Sheppard had discovered twelve of the 79 Jovian satellites , including Tuesday 's ten , mostly using a Blanco 4-meter telescope of Chile 's Cerro Tololo Inter-American Observatory .
#Text=The observatory is operated by the National Optical Astronomy Observatory in the US .
#Text=The tiny satellites , none more than five kilometres in diameter , were first observed in 2017 .
#Text=Orbits of these new Jovian satellites were calculated by International Astronomical Union 's Minor Planet Center 's Gareth Williams .
#Text=Williams explained , " It takes several observations to confirm an object actually orbits around Jupiter [ ... ]

#Text=Sheppard said ,  Jupiter just happened to be in the sky near the search fields where we were looking for extremely distant Solar System objects , so we were serendipitously able to look for new moons around Jupiter while at the same time looking for planets at the fringes of our Solar System " .

column1: #Text=Of the twelve satellites discovered by the team , nine were found to be retrograde , revolving around the gas giant in the direction opposite to the planet 's spin .
#Text=These nine new retrograde satellites take about two years to complete one revolution around Jupiter .
#Text=The remaining three satellites were prograde , spinning in the same direction as Jupiter 's rotation .

#Text=One of the prograde satellites , newly announced on Tuesday , took about one-and-half years to complete one revolution around Jupiter , and its orbit intersected with the outer retrograde satellites .
#Text=Sheppard said , " Our other discovery is a real oddball and has an orbit like no other known Jovian moon [ ... ]

#Text= Valetudo " is the name suggested for the " oddball " satellite .

column1: #Text=Valetudo was the Roman god Jupiter 's great-granddaughter , regarded as the goddess of health and hygiene .
#Text=Sheppard said , " Jupiter is like a big vacuum cleaner because it is so massive " .
#Text=Jupiter is the largest planet in the Solar System , with a diameter about 142,984 kilometres .
#Text=The largest known satellite in the Solar System is Jupiter 's Ganymede , whose diameter is approximately 5268 kilometres .
#Text=Saturn has the second-most known satellites : 62 , while Uranus has 27 .
